                            <comment id="13039078" author="dlofthouse" created="Tue, 10 Feb 2015 07:47:36 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;I think a better solution would be an &apos;allow-same-origin&apos; option otherwise there is going to be an additional attribute administrators need to update in parallel to their network configuration and bind address.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13039218" author="harald.pehl" created="Tue, 10 Feb 2015 13:13:10 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFCORE-536&quot; title=&quot;Sanitize origins  ports in CORS&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WFCORE-536&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WFCORE-536&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; takes care of this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13039446" author="ehugonnet" created="Wed, 11 Feb 2015 04:10:27 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;Until &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFCORE-536&quot; title=&quot;Sanitize origins  ports in CORS&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WFCORE-536&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WFCORE-536&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; you may add &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:9990&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:9990&lt;/a&gt; in the allowed origins list as a workaround.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
